url: "https://github.com/<your-org-or-username>/dbai"
abstract: >
  DBAI (Domain-Based Agent Identity) defines a lightweight, anchor-based identity discovery
  convention that uses domain namespaces as persistent rendezvous points for digital actors
  and AI agents. The project focuses on minimal identity semantics, decentralized resolution,
  and domain-scoped extension namespaces, enabling cross-platform actor discoverability
  without imposing credential or capability models.
keywords:
  - identity
  - agent identity
  - decentralized identity
  - DNS
  - AI agents
  - discovery
